es by pressing down with your fingertips or a fork. Make two slits in the center of the pastry to allow steam to escape, then bake for 40-50 minutes (200°C) or until pastry is golden brown. Serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Gluten free pastry","content":["160 g butter, unsalted, chilled, plus extra for greasing","140 g rice flour","160 g cornflour (starch), plus extra for dusting","¼ tsp fine salt","2 tsp xanthan gum (optional)","1 egg","1 tsp vinegar","40 g water, chilled"]},{"title":"Chicken and pear filling","content":["2 garlic cloves","1 leek, white part only, cut into pieces","50 g butter, unsalted","600 g chicken meat, skinless, boneless, cut into cubes (3 cm) (see tip)","3 sprigs fresh thyme, leaves only","½ tsp black pepper, freshly ground","50 g water","2 - 3 tbsp cornflour (starch)","1 tbsp vegetable stock paste","50 g white wine","150 g pear (approx. 1 pear), peeled, core removed and cut into cubes (2 cm)","50 g whipping cream"]}],"id":"r127581","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-2iXBRzuSBNk\/XZaoFfc7HwI\/AAAAAAAAhG4\/B1siTbBUTqQBVeGiDkmZvqS7V-vUUSDRgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_e_YISWpRnn_Z4mVj.png","title":"Chicken and pear pie","publishedAt":"2017-08-08T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"14.5 g","fat":"39.8 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"38.2 g","calories":"2386 kJ \/ 568 kcal"},"usefulItems":"deep pie dish (Ø 23 cm), baking paper, rolling pin, ceramic or glass bowl, silicone mat, cling film, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Blind baking is the process of baking a pie crust without the filling to keep pie crust from becoming soggy. Prick pastry base with a fork, line with baking paper and baking weights (e. g. dried beans) and bake as indicated in the recipe.","Use boneless and skinless chicken thighs or chicken breast fillets. Chicken thigh meat will add more flavour to the filling, though.","Serve Chicken and pear pie as a hearty meal with your favourite steamed vegetables or salad on the side.","Leftovers store well in a sealable container in the refrigerator for lunches the next day.","To ensure gluten free recipes are gluten free, always read the labels of your products as some may contain traces of wheat or gluten."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","2h 40m","8 portions"]}